Information Recovery:

1. Treat dropped pairs P̄ = {(i,j) ∉ P} as a structured missingness problem
2. Train a lightweight residual recovery module that estimates what sparse attention missed
3. Use the hash bucket logits ℓQ, ℓK as a proxy for "how confident" the model is about what it dropped
4. Recovery signal can come from: diffusion, spectral gap, or a secondary low-rank approximation

Primary focus :
(1) sparse efficiency via LSH, 
(2) principled recovery of dropped cross-node information.